description.narrative: By 2022, in UNICEF supported states, government and partner institutions have strengthened systems for multi-sector coordination, planning, monitoring, and human resource development for nutrition, which contributes to Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

description.narrative: In 2019 The Government directed all states to create a multi-sectoral nutrition committee to guide the National Nutrition Mission. Only twelve out of 14 UNICEF supported statesmanaged to implement but all 14 states created nutrition committees chaired by the principal secretary or similar level authority. Quarterly meetings multi-sectoral nutrition were planned. Twelve out of 14 states completed state level Convergence Action Plans that included of key performance indicators, annual targets, convergent strategies, monitoring tools and detailed action plans. Nine out of 14 (64%) states held multi-sectoral nutrition mission meetings at least twice a year. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:01/01/2020
